    <briefdescription>
<para>FreeType-based implementation of `FontResourceProvider` for OpenGL. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>`FreeTypeFontResourceManager` uses the FreeType library to load TrueType fonts, rasterize glyphs, and cache them as OpenGL textures. Each glyph is stored as a separate texture for simplicity.</para>
<para>## Responsibilities</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>**Font Loading:** Parse font files using FreeType and extract glyph metrics.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>**Texture Creation:** Upload glyph bitmaps to GPU as GL_R8 textures.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>**Caching:** Store glyph data per font for efficient repeated access.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>**Resource Cleanup:** Delete OpenGL textures when the manager is destroyed.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>## Usage</para>
<para>```cpp <ref refid="classhelios_1_1ext_1_1opengl_1_1rendering_1_1FreeTypeFontResourceManager" kindref="compound">FreeTypeFontResourceManager</ref> fontManager; fontManager.loadFont(FontId{&quot;roboto&quot;}, &quot;fonts/Roboto-Regular.ttf&quot;);</para>
<para>// Retrieve a glyph for rendering Glyph g = fontManager.glyph(&apos;A&apos;, FontId{&quot;roboto&quot;}); ```</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Currently loads ASCII characters 0-127 with a fixed pixel size of 24.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para>FontResourceProvider </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para>Glyph </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1ext_1_1opengl_1_1rendering_1_1OpenGLGlyphTextRenderer" kindref="compound">OpenGLGlyphTextRenderer</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
